                        <handDesc hands="1">
                            <summary>Two (perhaps three?) different hands; possibly <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name>'s brother,
                                    <name type="person" key="JonMag011">Jón Magnússon</name> and
                                    <name type="person" key="JonArn005">Jón Arnórsson</name>.
                                According to <name type="person" key="JonOla003">Jón
                                Ólafsson</name>'s catalogue (<ref type="ms" target="AM02-456-da">AM
                                    456 fol.</ref>): 'med hende Jons Magnuſsonar i <name type="place" key="SólSta02">Solheimum</name> og Jons Arnorſsonar
                                i <name type="place" key="LjáLax01">Liäskogom</name> ad eg
                                meina'.</summary>
                            <handNote scope="major" script="unknown" scribe="JonMag011"/>
                            <handNote scope="major" script="unknown" scribe="JonArn005"/>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>On the first of the three first flyleaves a hand from <date from="1790" to="1810">c. 1800</date> added: <q xml:lang="is">Þetta
                                er exſcriptum membranæ, ſem A. Magnæus kallar Olafsſögu fra Bæ
                                fylgir ad meſtu leiti ordrett Snorra Sturluſyni, og hefir hun
                                allvida hialpad mer med margar godar variantes.</q>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="false">
                                <p>Bound in a half-binding with parchment spine and corners; the
                                    boards are covered in marbled paper. <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> wrote the title on the
                                    spine but that is now almost worn off.</p>
                                <p>Previously, the boards were covered in written parchment from a
                                        <title>Lectionarium brevarii</title> in Latin (<country key="IS">Island</country>, <date notBefore="1300" notAfter="1399">s. XIV</date>). <name type="person" key="OttEhl001">Otto Ehlert</name> removed it in the summer
                                    of <date when="1911">1911</date>; it is now transferred to <ref type="ms" target="Acc-0007-c-da">Access. 7c, Hs. 91</ref>
                                    ff. 2-3.</p>
                            </binding>
